The paper proposes a new end-to-end single image dehazing method using a deep learning approach. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a new edge-preserving loss function and a joint-discriminator based on generative adversarial network framework, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method also involves multi-level pyramid pooling module, which is related to graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method using extensive experiments, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
